    <item>
      <title>Prescription drugs are the 3rd cause of all US deaths, 4th  cause of  deaths in hospital</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/prescription-drugs-are-the-3rd-cause-of-all-us-deaths-4th-cause-of-deaths-in-hospital/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 18 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/prescription-drugs-are-the-3rd-cause-of-all-us-deaths-4th-cause-of-deaths-in-hospital/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h4 id=&#34;prescription-drugs-are-the-leading-cause-of-death&#34;&gt;Prescription Drugs Are the Leading Cause of Death&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://brownstone.org/articles/prescription-drugs-are-the-leading-cause-of-death/?utm_source=substack&amp;amp;utm_medium=email&#34;&gt;Brownstone&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;37,309 drug deaths were reported to the FDA in 2006 and&lt;br&gt;&#xA;123,927 ten years later, which is 3.3 times as many&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Depression drugs kill many people, mainly among the elderly, because they can cause orthostatic hypotension, sedation, confusion, and dizziness. The drugs double the risk of falls and hip fractures in a dose-dependent manner,8,9 and within one year after a hip fracture, about one-fifth of the patients will have died. As elderly people often fall anyway, it is not possible to know if such deaths are drug deaths.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
