    <item>
      <title>Rare diseases: 1 in 10 Americans (some are helped by Vitamin D) - 2023</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/rare-diseases-1-in-10-americans-some-are-helped-by-vitamin-d-2023/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 29 Sep 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/rare-diseases-1-in-10-americans-some-are-helped-by-vitamin-d-2023/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;There are more than 10,000 known rare diseases.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Approximately 80% of rare diseases are estimated to have a genetic origin.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Of those, 70% start in childhood.  (56% of rare diseases start in childhood)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&amp;ldquo;In the United States, about half of the people with a rare disease are children. Many of these diseases are chronic and worsen over time.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The US defines incidence of a &amp;ldquo;rare disease&amp;rdquo; as being 1 in every 1,500 people&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
